ement learnerships.To be accredited, a training provider mustdevelop a curriculum for the learnership according to the standards of the South African Qualifications Authority ;follow sound education, training and development practices; andregister as an Education and Training Development Practitioner .Training providers and the employers that will give practical experience have to agree onhow many learners they will train;criteria to choose learners; andhow they will find learners.Learners can be already employed workers of the employer or unemployed people.Contact the nearest labour centre to find out how the Department of Labour can help you find unemployed learners.Training providers must start training on the date agreed on in the learnership agreement.Skills Development Act, 1998It may take up to 30 days to set up a learnership.Apply at the Department of Labour.Home > Your Government > Provincial Government of the Western Cape > Speeches > Provincial Government of the Western Cape - Speeches Archive: June 2005PROVINCIAL GOVERNMENT OF THE WESTERN CAPE - SPEECHES ARCHIVE: JUNE 2005The content on this page was last updated on 21 July 2005The tourist guide is the first person to make contact with the visitor who sets foot on our shores.This includes access to finance to initiate BEE deals and ownership, but also providing services and skills to manage and sustain BEE after the deals are made.Request for tax deduction directive ‚Äì retirement annuity fundThe request must be submitted when a person has reached retirement age and wishes to exercise benefits accrued in a retirement annuity policy.This request may also be made if a member wishes to transfer his or her benefits under one retirement annuity fund to another retirement annuity fund.Complete the tax deduction form and submit to SARS.The following minimum application information is required to process a directive application:taxpayer's initialstaxpayer's date of birthtaxpayer's ID n