rs, that sell seed.All available seed lots, that is both commercial and certified seed, are taken into consideration.Seed lots to be sampled are chosen as follows:a random choice of seed lotssuspect seed lotsproblematic crop types.Samples are tested for compliance with the provisions of the Plant Improvement Act such as purity and germination or viability.Auditors are notified of results.When results show that the seed is not in compliance with the Act, it may be withdrawn from sale or re-labeled.As this seed testing service is rendered in terms of national legislation, no service fee is charged.However, if the person from whom the sample is taken requests the test result in the form of a Seed Analysis Report, a treasury approved seed testing tariff must be paid.An invoice will be issued.Banking details are:Bank : Standard BankBranch name : ArcadiaBranch code : 01-08-45Account number : 011244887Account name : NDA: Seed Testing ServicesRemember to include the invoice number in order that it may be reconciled with the issued invoice.The Official Seed Testing Station uses a priority system for testing.As the various crop types have different test conditions, the duration of a test can vary from a few days to a few weeks.Make enquiries at the facility itself .Umphandle > Ushicilelo > IiNkcukacha Zoluntu: VIINKCUKACHA ZOLUNTU: VValue-Added Tax Refund Procedure (ifumaneka ngesiNgesi kuphela)(Uhlobo loxwebhu: pdf; ubukhulu: 657 KB)Victim Empowerment Programme (ifumaneka ngesiNgesi kuphela)Home > Publications > Public Information > W > You and Maintenance: Maintenance is in the Best Interests of the Child &gt Maintenance is in the Best Interests of the ChildHome > Publications > Public Information > W > You and Maintenance: Maintenance is in the Best Interests of the Child &gt What Can I Do to Protect the Best Interests of Children when it Comes to Maintenance?Home > Publications > Public Information > W > You and Maintenance: Maintenance is in 