Governments have a political and an administrative arm.The political arm creates the laws and policies.Citizens elect representatives to the national parliament, the provincial parliament and the local councils.The Administrative arm is the part of government that implements laws and provides services.It consists of all the Departments (e.g. Health, Agriculture).The governments that are relevant to the Western Cape are:* The Government of South Africa* Provincial Government of the Western CapeHome > Your Government > Provincial Government of the Western Cape > Department of Cultural Affairs & Sport > CommitteesDEPARTMENT OF CULTURAL AFFAIRS & SPORT: COMMITTEESThe following committees operate in the Department:Home > Your Government > Provincial Government of the Western Cape > Department of Cultural Affairs & Sport > ContactDEPARTMENT OF CULTURAL AFFAIRS & SPORT: CONTACTProtea Assurance Bldg, Green Market Square, Cape Town, 8000Sport:Camern PietersTel: 021 483 9622Fax: 021 483 9623Email: Capieter@pgwc.gov.zaCultureLoretta GoodmanTel: 021 483 9672Email: Lgoodman@pgwc.gov.zaAdministrationPhilasande MacwiliTel: 021 483 9517Fax: 021 483 9521Home > Your Government > Provincial Government of the Western Cape > Department of Cultural Affairs & Sport > Facilities > Regional Sports and Recreation OfficesDEPARTMENT OF CULTURAL AFFAIRS & SPORT - FACILITIES: REGIONAL SPORTS AND RECREATION OFFICESHome > Your Government > Provincial Government of the Western Cape > Department of Cultural Affairs & Sport > Facilities > Museum SchoolsDEPARTMENT OF CULTURAL AFFAIRS & SPORT - FACILITIES: MUSEUM SCHOOLSHome > Your Government > Provincial Government of the Western Cape > Department of Cultural Affairs & Sport > Facilities > Sports & RecreationDEPARTMENT OF CULTURAL AFFAIRS & SPORT - FACILITIES: SPORTS & RECREATIONHome > Your Government > Provincial Government of the Western Cape > Department of Cultural Affairs & Sport > FacilitiesDEPARTMENT OF CULTUR