h similar bodies;enter into joint ventures with other institutions, organisations, municipalities, bodies or persons;become partners or shareholders in companies, close corporations or other bodies and to sell all or part of such shares or interests; andraise funds through donations and sponsorships;liaise with any other entity, organ of state, organisation or institution whose activities or aims have an impact on and relate to the development, promotion or marketing of investment in the Province;investigate and make recommendations to the Executive Council, through the responsible Member of the Executive Council on any matter relating directly or indirectly to the promotion, development or marketing of investment in the Province;enter into agreements for the attainment of its objects, the exercise of its powers, duties and functions or the management and administration of its affairs, whether or not expressly provided for in this section; anddo any other thing or attend to any other matter that the responsible Member of the Executive Council considers necessary for the proper implementation of this Act.In addition to the powers referred to in subsection, the Agency, has the powers referred to in section 34 of, and Schedule 2 to, the Companies Act, 1973 .The Board consists of ‚Äïat least five, but not more than 20, members appointed by the responsible Member of the Executive Council; andthe Chief Executive Officer, ex officio, as contemplated in section 17.Members of the Board must be fit and proper persons to serve the best interests of the Province, collectively possessing ‚Äïappropriate knowledge or experience in organised constituencies within the business industry; andthe following skills and expertise ‚Äïlegal skills, experience and qualifications;financial skills, experience and qualifications;investment and export experience or qualifications;labour market experience or qualifications;human resource or educational experience or qualifications;community development skills and experience; andplanning or development skills and experience.In appointing members to the Board, the responsible Member of the Executive Council must ensure that ‚Äïhistoric imbalances are addressed;the Board, collectively possess the necessary and appropriate skills and expertise;the Board is representative of persons employed or involved in the import, export, trade and investment business enterprises in the Province;municipal interests are represented on the Board in such a manner that equitable spatial representation of municipalities is achieved: Provided that no more than four persons may be appointed to the Board to give effect to the provisions of this paragraph; andorganised local government is represented on the Board.The responsible Member of the Executive Council-must designateone of the members of the Board as the Chairperson of the Board; andone of the members of the Board as the Deputy Chairperson of the Board.the nomination procedure;the requirements for nomination; andthe closing date for the nomination.van die aangestelde lede insluitend die termyn van hul aanstelling.A person is disqualified from being appointed to the Board or from remaining on the Board, by reason that he or she ‚Äïis directly or indirectly interested in any contract with the Agency and fails to declare his or her interest and the nature thereof in the manner required by this Act;is a person under curatorship;has at any time been removed from an office of trust on account of misconduct involving theft or fraud;has been convicted and sentenced to a term of imprisonment without the option of a fine, except that the responsible Member of the Executive Council may, upon a person who is nominated for appointment disclosing full details of an offence in an affidavit, condone a conviction in a manner that is consistent with section 106 of the Constitution: Provided that a disqualification in terms of this subsection ends five years after the sentence has been completed; andfails to disclose an interest in accordance with section 7 or attended or participated in the proceedings of the Board while having an interest contemplated in the said section;A person who has been nominated to serve on the Board in terms of subsection 5 must, within ten days of being nominated, submit a written declaration to the responsible Member of the Executive Council of all direct or indirect interests in any company or other business interests.Any failure by the nominee to disclose financial and other interests in terms of subsection disqualifies such nominee in terms of section 6 to be considered for the position of the member of the Board.Every member of the Board must, upon assuming office and at the beginning of every financial year of the Agency, submit a written declaration of his or her direct or indirect interest in any company or other business interest in the manner provided for in section 234 of the Companies Act, 1973 .Where a member of the Board acquires interest in any company or other business interests, at anytime during his or her tenure as a member of the Board, he or she must, within ten days of the date of the acquisition of such an interest, submit a written declaration to the responsible Member of the Executive Council of such an interest.Any failure on the part of the member to disclose his or her interest as contemplated in subsections and may result in the termination of appointment of such member in terms of section 10.The responsible Member of the Executive Council must keep an updated register of the interests of members of the Board disclosed in terms of this section.A member of the Board who fails to make a declaration envisaged in section 7 may, subject to subsection be disqualified from remaining on the Board.The responsible Member of the Executive Council, on becoming aware that a member of the Board has failed to comply with the provisions of section 7, must investigate