anes , enabling more runs in the busy peak periods good working conditions for employees , with better pay , training , shorter hours and more career opportunitiesa bigger market for public transport as people switch from private cars to the new systemthe new system offers existing operators an opportunity to grow their businesses , and participate in a new system that will change our city for the better .the city of cape town sees those minibus taxi and bus operators whose services will be upgraded by the irt , as preferred partners .already , operators in the minibus taxi industry have started to grow and diversify their businesses , taking up opportunities in tourism , and learner and student transport .some have even expanded into related industries , including fuel stations , vehicle dealerships , parts and maintenance .the minibus taxi industry is maturing , and the entrepreneurs who lead it have shown that they can build and expand their businesses .as the city of cape town moves ahead with integrated rapid transit , it is looking for a strong partnership with existing operators in planning and developing the system , and ultimately becoming the operators of the new service .the existing minibus and bus industries must have a voice in shaping the new system .their expertise will be important in delivering a quality product to the customer .increased profitabilitythe new system will deliver increased profitability for operators .this will be achieved through dedicated lanes , a better fuel economy , bulk buying of new kinds of vehicles and parts , and coordinated marketing and advertising to attract new customers .a level playing fieldthe minibus taxi industry has never received operating subsidies from government .there has long been a sense of unfairness , as some operators are compensated , while others are not .in the new business model , all operators will be treated equally on a level playing field .in addition , government will provide 